text=(:Title Mage Character Creation:)%0a[[#mtop]]%0a[[GameRef.MageCharacterCreation?action=edit|Click here to Edit]]%0a%0a(:table border=0 style=float width=40%25 align=right  cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr align=center:)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a(:cellnr bgcolor=#1b9ad0 align=center:)%0a[[#Staff]][+%25color=#FFE400%25'''Contents'''+]%0a(:cellnr:) %0a*[[#Creation| Character Creation]]%0a*[[#Restricted| Restricted]]%0a*[[#ixp| Incentive XP]]%0a*[[#BannedMerits| Banned Merit List]]%0a*[[#UpdateThreads| Character Update Threads]]%0a*[[#ProximiRules| Proximus Rules]]%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a[[#Creation]]%0a%25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Character Creation'''++]\\%0a\\%0a%0a* Please follow the [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/pmwiki/index.php?n=GameRef.CharacterCreation | General Character Creation Guidelines]]%0a* Please follow this format when naming your PC: ~Shadowname~ First Name Last Name.%0a* Concepts should follow modern day themes, sorry no ninja assassins.%0a* 3 dots in Gnosis will need excellent justification as to why your PC is shrugging off the Fallen World and has gotten closer to their Supernal self and Watchtower. %0a* Legacies will not be available at Character Creation, they must be attained IC through a Mentor (which you can purchase at Character Generation.)%0a* No specific knowledge of other Supernatural creatures and/or PCs allowed beyond what your [[OccultLore|Occult skill]] indicates. Spirits and Ghosts are excluded from this.%0a* High Speech will be given for free if you have Status in an Order. If you are not a part of any Order, High Speech can be purchased for the Merit cost and it must be explained in the background how your PC learned it.%0a* No Arcana above 3 dots will be allowed.%0a* You may begin the game with rotes from the Core Rulebook, Tome of Mysteries, and your Order book.\\%0a%0a[--%25color=#1b9ad0%25[[#mtop| Back to top]]--]\\%0a\\%0a%0a    %0a[[#Restricted]]%0a%25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Restricted List'''++]\\%0a\\%0a%0aYour character has three restricted slots that apply both for mage specific restricted items and general restricted items. It should be noted that most restricted slots require justification.%0a* If your awakened character is from San Diego, they may not have Order Status higher then one dot. If your awakened character is from outside San Diego, they may have two dots of status. This is a restricted slot.%0a* A skill at four dots costs mages two restricted slots rather than one.%0a* Gnosis 3 is one restricted slot, Gnosis 2 is not restricted.%0a* The Mage Venue follows the General Restricted Slots found [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/pmwiki/index.php?n=GameRef.CharacterCreation| here]].\\%0a%0a[--%25color=#1b9ad0%25[[#mtop| Back to top]]--]\\%0a\\%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#BannedMerits]]%0a%25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Banned Merits List'''++]\\%0a\\%0a%0a%0a[--%25color=#1b9ad0%25[[#mtop| Back to top]]--]\\%0a\\%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#ixp]]%0a%25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Mage Venue Incentive XP'''++]\\%0a\\%0a%0a'''Players may have a maximum of +5 Venue iXP and +5 WoD iXP at creation '''%0a%0a[[http://www.wantonwicked.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=250&t=32374 | General iXP]]%0a%0a'''Setting:'''\\%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a[--%25color=#1b9ad0%25[[#mtop| Back to top]]--]\\%0a\\%0a%0a%0a[[#UpdateThreads]]%0a%25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Character Update Threads'''++]\\%0a\\%0a%0aCharacter Update Threads are a very important part of Wanton Wicked! Character Update Threads allow players to communicate with STs, leave records of what there character has done or will do, and request scenes or expenditure of experience points! After you have been sanctioned, create the a thread in the [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/forum/viewforum.php?f=428| Mage Character Threads]] section of the forum with a title in the following format: [Order] ~Shadowname~ First Name Last Name. Remember, this will be your primary method of communicating with the Storytellers so don't forget to check back often!\\%0a%0a[--%25color=#1b9ad0%25[[#mtop| Back to top]]--]\\%0a%0a%0a[[#ProximiRules]]%0a%25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Proximi Rules'''++]\\%0a\\%0a%0aSo!  Here are the new rules for making a Proximi in the Mage 3.0 venue!%0a%0a* You do not need to purchase the Sleepwalker or Proximi merit.  However, you must purchase the Unseen Sense (Supernal) merit.%0a%0a* Access to S.S. powers are a restricted slot, and requires extensive background justification.  Second Sight powers are NOT Supernal magic.   There needs to be a ''very'' strong reason why you have two kinds of magic.  You will also suffer prejudice.%0a%0a* Proximi have their own set of iXP:  %0a-> for using a [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/pmwiki/index.php?n=GameRef.Dynasty|pre-approved Dynasty]].%0a%0a%0a%0a[--%25color=#1b9ad0%25[[#mtop| Back to top]]--]\\%0a%0a%0a%0a(:include CityBook.MageNavigationBar:)
