diff:1372686339:1372653904:=56c56,62%0a%3c %0a---%0a> * Artifact: Banned at CC due to power level and themes.%0a> * Athenaeum: Banned at CC because of storyline.%0a> * Order Status: Restricted because of storyline, must be an out-of-towner to take at 2, banned at 3+.%0a> * Consilium status: Banned because of storyline.%0a> * Thrall: Banned because it's stupid.%0a> * Hallow: Banned at CC because of storyline.\\%0a> %0a72,74c78,92%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> It may seem odd that the Mage team is offering an incentive for playing a concept that isn't as highly rewarded generally, but hear us out. The setting, as you've probably been able to glean from the capsule, is about rebuilding and opportunity. As JasonA put it, "there's Mana in them thar hills." It's a Mage gold rush. We want to see concepts that embrace that feeling. We'll be getting some squibs to detail the setting in other major CA areas very shortly.%0a> %0a> * 2 BXP for a compelling NPC created in a backstory, allowed once.%0a> * 2 BXP for being a Pentacle Mage.%0a> * 2 BXP for being a newcomer to San Diego from another California area or from the Tijuana area/ 1 BXP for being a newcomer from another area in the United States or Northern Mexico.%0a> %0a> %0a> '''Lex Magica:'''\\%0a> %0a> In order to create a decent body of precedent for the Lex from the start of the game, xp is being offered for writing up individual cases. It should be short, no longer than two paragraphs, and should mention the legal issue at play, the factual circumstances, and the result. We retain discretion to amend any precedents offered, but as long as they aren't flat-out rejected, you'll still get your bonus.%0a> %0a> * 1 BXP per precedent written, to a max of 3.%0a> %0a> '''Maximum: +5BXP'''\\%0a> %0a99,102c117,123%0a%3c -> for using a [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/pmwiki/index.php?n=GameRef.Dynasty|pre-approved Dynasty]].%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> ->+2 for using a [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/pmwiki/index.php?n=GameRef.Dynasty|pre-approved Dynasty]].%0a> ->+3 for being associated with the Silver Ladder.%0a> ->+1 for story hooks related to mages.%0a> %0a> * No concepts that revolve around being ignorant of the Awakened.%0a> %0a> * New Dynasties are no longer permitted.   They take far too much time to deal with when we need to devote time to other pressing matters.%0a
